TY  - JOUR
AU  - Landry, Peter
T1  - Bad Habits and the Endogenous Timing of Urges
PY  - 2019
Y1  - 2019/03/01
DO  - 10.1093/restud/rdx079
JO  - The Review of Economic Studies
JA  - Rev Econ Stud
VL  - 86
IS  - 2
SP  - 785
EP  - 806
SN  - 0034-6527
AB  - I present a theory of harmful addiction in which “giving in” to an unwanted urge ($i.e.$ consumption) delays the recurrence of urges in the short-run, but increases their long-run frequency. The theory offers new predictions as to how the frequency, levels, cue-dependence, and temporal consistency of consumption evolve during habituation, while uniquely capturing near-term substitution in demand across time. New welfare implications for restrictions on consumption and on marketing are also addressed.
Y2  - 3/25/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1093/restud/rdx079
ER  - 



