TY  - JOUR
AU  - Sinkinson, Michael
AU  - Starc, Amanda
T1  - Ask Your Doctor? Direct-to-Consumer Advertising of Pharmaceuticals
PY  - 2019
Y1  - 2019/03/01
DO  - 10.1093/restud/rdy001
JO  - The Review of Economic Studies
JA  - Rev Econ Stud
VL  - 86
IS  - 2
SP  - 836
EP  - 881
SN  - 0034-6527
AB  - We measure the impact of direct-to-consumer television advertising (DTCA) by drug manufacturers. Our identification strategy exploits shocks to local advertising markets generated by the political advertising cycle and a regulatory intervention affecting a single product. We find evidence of significant business stealing effects among branded, advertised drugs. In addition, we show positive spillovers from drug advertisements to non-advertised competitors in the same class. We decompose the effect and show it is primarily due to new customers. Finally, we provide evidence that DTCA is cost-effective from a societal standpoint in our setting.
Y2  - 3/25/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1093/restud/rdy001
ER  - 



